summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 1999 CHEVROLET TRACKER.  THE AIR CONDITIONER IN HER VEHICLE WOULD NOT WORK.  THE DEALER REPLACED THE COMPRESSOR, CONDENSER, AND THE VACUUM HOWEVER; THE AIR CONDITIONER WOULD NOT WORK.  THE COST OF THE REPAIRS WAS $6,000.  SHE WAS ALSO ADVISED THAT THE FAN NEEDED TO BE REPLACED AND THE COST OF THE REPAIRS WAS $700.  THE FAILURE HAS BEEN ONGOING SINCE AUGUST 2005.  THE CURRENT MILEAGE WAS 96,000 AND THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 86,000.  THE VEHICLE DATE OF PURCHASE AND DEALER ADDRESS INFORMATION WAS UNAVAILABLE.
